value.value: 房室中隔形態異常
any structural anomaly of the wall of the heart that separates the right atrium and left ventricle; and is located just above the septal cusp of the tricuspid valve
大動脈弁尖の肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the aortic valve cusp thickness to the aortic wall thickness
大動脈弁の肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the aortic valve wall thickness to the aortic wall thickness
大動脈弁尖の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the three fibrous triangular components and associated flap of the aortic valve
大動脈一尖弁
the presence of one cusp and associated flap in the aortic valve instead of three
大動脈弁尖の欠如
absence of the three fibrous triangular components and associated flaps of the aortic valve
大動脈弁輪形態異常

any structural anomaly of the fibrous ring of the aortic valve that attaches the cusps of aortic valve to the wall of left ventricle, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the posterior, right anterior and left anterior cusps
胎仔共通房室管中隔形成異常

anomaly in the process by which the dorsal and ventral endocardial cushions develop in the walls of the common atrioventricular canal, grow toward each other and fuse, dividing the common atrioventricular canal into right and left atrioventricular canals and the atrioventricular septum
肺動脈弁肥大
an increase in the total area occupied by the pulmonary valve
肺動脈弁肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the pulmonary valve wall thickness to the pulmonary artery wall thickness
肺動脈弁尖の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the three fibrous triangular components and associated flap of the pulmonary valve
肺動脈一尖弁
the presence of one cusp and associated flap in the pulmonary valve instead of three
肺動脈弁尖の欠如
absence of the three fibrous triangular components and associated flaps of the pulmonary valve
肺動脈弁尖の肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the pulmonary valve cusp thickness to the pulmonary artery wall thickness
肺動脈弁輪の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the fibrous ring of the pulmonary valve that attaches the cusps of pulmonary valve to the wall of right ventricle, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the anterior, right posterior and left posterior cusps
総房室弁
the presence of a single atrioventricular valve instead of both a mitral and tricuspid valve, most commonly due to incomplete or failure of fetal atrioventricular canal septation
腱索の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the tendinous strands that connect the papillary muscles on the wall of the ventricles to the leaflets of the atrioventricular valves; the chordae tendineae serve to prevent the AV valves from prolapsing back into the atria
腱索の欠如

absence of the tendinous strands that connect the papillary muscles on the wall of the ventricles to the leaflets of the atrioventricular valves; the chordae tendineae serve to prevent the AV valves from prolapsing back into the atria
大動脈弁開存
the aortic valve remains open during the cardiac cycle
肺動脈弁開存
the pulmonary valve remains open during the cardiac cycle
特発性肥大性大動脈弁下狭窄症
abnormal narrowing, constriction or obstruction of the left ventricular outflow tract due to hypertrophy of the interventricular septum, which results in obstruction to blood flow
僧帽弁輪の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the fibrous ring of the mitral valve that attaches the cusps of mitral valve to the heart, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the anterior and posterior cusps
僧帽弁尖の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the two fibrous components and associated flaps of the mitral valve
単尖僧帽弁
the presence of one cusp and associated flap in the mitral valve instead of two
僧帽弁尖の欠如
absence of the two fibrous components and associated flaps of the mitral valve
僧帽弁尖の肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the mitral valve cusp wall thickness to the atrioventricular septum thickness
僧帽弁肥大
an increase in the total area occupied by the mitral valve
僧帽弁開存
the mitral valve remains open during the cardiac cycle
僧帽弁肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the mitral valve wall thickness to the atrioventricular septum thickness
三尖弁輪の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the fibrous ring of the tricuspid valve that attaches the cusps of tricuspid valve to the heart, and which consists of portions of the fibrous scallops of the anterior cusp (infundibular cusp), the posterior cusp (marginal cusp), and the septal cusp (medial cusp)
三尖弁尖の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the three fibrous triangular components and associated flaps of the tricuspid valve
二尖性三尖弁
the presence of two cusps and associated flaps in the tricuspid valve instead of three
単尖性三尖弁
the presence of one cusp and associated flap in the tricuspid valve instead of three
三尖弁尖の欠如
absence of the three fibrous triangular components and associated flaps of the tricuspid valve
三尖弁尖の肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the tricuspid valve cusp wall thickness to the atrioventricular septum thickness
三尖弁肥大
an increase in the total area occupied by the tricuspid valve
三尖弁の開存
the tricuspid valve remains open during the cardiac cycle
三尖弁の肥厚
an increase in the ratio of the tricuspid valve wall thickness to the atrioventricular septum thickness
心筋組織の形態異常

any structural anomaly of the involuntary muscle comprising the myocardium of the heart and the walls of the pulmonary veins and superior vena cava; cardiac muscle is striated and multinucleate, and the cardiomyocytes branch and are joined to one another via intercalated discs

definition.value: Do not confuse cardiac muscle tissue with the myocardium. Myocardium consists primarily of cardiac muscle but these structures are not identical. Cardiac muscle tissue also exists outside the heart so this term has not been made a child of heart myocardial layer directly.

value.value: Q波振幅の増大
increase in the size (height or maximum displacement) of the downward deflection in the ECG occurring after the PR interval that represents depolarization of the interventricular septum
心筋壊死
morphological changes resulting from pathological death of cardiomyocytes or a portion of the cardiac muscle tissue; usually due to irreversible damage
心筋肥大
an increase in size of the myocardium, not due to increased cell number
QRS振幅の増大

increased in the size (height or maximum displacement) of the largest-amplitude portion of the ECG, caused by currents generated when the ventricles depolarize prior to their contraction, suggesting ventricular excitation defects
大動脈肺側副動脈

small ectopic arteries or arterial branches that connect the aorta, aortic branches and/or subclavian artery regions directly to the lung parenchyma, usually seen in conjunction with pulmonary atresia, ventricular septal defect (VSD) and/or closed ductus arteriosus
脚ブロック

intraventricular block resulting from an interruption or partial or complete block of conduction in one of the two atrioventricular bundle branches; a prolonged QRS complex seen on an ECG indicates defects in bundle branch conduction; blocks in each branch result in a distinct QRS ECG waveform morphology
洞性徐脈
a type of decreased heart rhythm in which fewer than the normal number of impulses arise from the sinoatrial (SA) node
介在板の欠如
absence of the electron dense junctional complex, at the end to end contacts of cardiac muscle cells, that contains two types of membrane junctions i.e. gap junctions and desmosomes
腫瘍病理の変化
any changes associated with the chemistry, immunohistology, cellular alterations or environmental interactions of tumors compared to the expected state
心室心筋緻密層形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the ventricular myocardium compact layer, typically resulting in decreased size
下行大動脈狭窄
diffuse constriction or narrowing of the descending aorta
